# ─── FRONTEND ENV — copy to .env and fill in real values ─────────────────────
#
# KEY VISIBILITY TAXONOMY:
#
#  EXPO_PUBLIC_*    → inlined into the compiled JS bundle at build time.
#                     Anyone who downloads the app can read these.
#                     Only use for values that are genuinely non-secret
#                     (public Cognito IDs, your own API URL, region).
#
#  (no prefix)      → available to app.config.js at build time for injecting
#                     into native configs (AndroidManifest, Info.plist) only.
#                     Never inlined into the JS bundle.
#                     Use for the Maps SDK key and any other native-only keys.
#
#  SERVER-SIDE ONLY → never put these in this file. They live in backend/.env
#                     and are deployed to AWS Lambda via CDK environment vars.
#                       - ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
#                       - GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY (backend copy, for Places API proxy)

# ─── Native-build only (not in JS bundle) ────────────────────────────────────
# Restrict in Google Cloud Console:
#   iOS:     Bundle ID  com.roamly.app
#   Android: Package    com.roamly.app  + release SHA-1 fingerprint
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your-google-maps-api-key

# ─── Intentionally public (safe in JS bundle) ────────────────────────────────
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-api-gateway-url/v1
EXPO_PUBLIC_COGNITO_USER_POOL_ID=us-east-1_XXXXXXXX
EXPO_PUBLIC_COGNITO_CLIENT_ID=your-cognito-client-id
EXPO_PUBLIC_AWS_REGION=us-east-1
